@title The Owned contract
@notice A contract with helpers for basic contract ownership.

@dev Allows an owner to begin transferring ownership to a new address,
pending.
@dev Allows an ownership transfer to be completed by the recipient.
@dev Reverts if called by anyone other than the contract owner.

@notice Reads the current answer from aggregator delegated to.
   * @dev #[deprecated] Use latestRoundData instead. This does not error if no
answer has been reached, it will simply return 0. Either wait to point to
an already answered Aggregator or use the recommended latestRoundData
instead which includes better verification information.

@notice Reads the last updated height from aggregator delegated to.
   * @dev #[deprecated] Use latestRoundData instead. This does not error if no
answer has been reached, it will simply return 0. Either wait to point to
an already answered Aggregator or use the recommended latestRoundData
instead which includes better verification information.

@notice get the latest completed round where the answer was updated. This
ID includes the proxy's phase, to make sure round IDs increase even when
switching to a newly deployed aggregator.
   * @dev #[deprecated] Use latestRoundData instead. This does not error if no
answer has been reached, it will simply return 0. Either wait to point to
an already answered Aggregator or use the recommended latestRoundData
instead which includes better verification information.
@notice returns the current phase's aggregator address.
@notice returns the current phase's ID.
@notice represents the number of decimals the aggregator responses represent.

@notice the version number representing the type of aggregator the proxy
points to.
@notice returns the description of the aggregator the proxy points to.

@notice Allows the owner to propose a new address for the aggregator
@param _aggregator The new address for the aggregator contract

approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}.     * Requirements:     * - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

bet(bool,address,uint80,uint256).details: Open a new call or put options.

params.a_: the amount to spend on on the option
params.k_: type of option to buy (true for call )
params.pp_: the address of the price provider to use (must be in the list of aprvd from IAPP)
params.t_: the rounds until your options expiration (must be minT < t_ > maxT)

closeStaking().details: used to send this pool into EOL mode when a newer one is open

complete(uint256).details: exercise and expire functions have been depreciated in favor of this single complete option

params.oID: id of the option to complete

decimals().details: Returns the number of decimals used to get its user representation. For example, if `decimals` equals `2`, a balance of `505` tokens should be displayed to a user as `5,05` (`505 / 10 ** 2`).     * Tokens usually opt for a value of 18, imitating the relationship between Ether and Wei. This is the value {ERC20} uses, unless {_setupDecimals} is called.     * NOTE: This information is only used for _display_ purposes: it in no way affects any of the arithmetic of the contract, including {IERC20-balanceOf} and {IERC20-transfer}.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically decreases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller.     * This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}.     * Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance.     * Requirements:     * - `spender` cannot be the zero address. - `spender` must have allowance for the caller of at least `subtractedValue`.

getMaxAvailable().details: Get the largest amount a bet can be created for

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically increases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller.     * This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}.     * Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance.     * Requirements:     * - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

params.amount_: the amount you want to deposit to be used for underwriting options

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}.     * Requirements:     * - `recipient` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `amount`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}.     * Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20}.     * Requirements:     * - `sender` and `recipient` cannot be the zero address. - `sender` must have a balance of at least `amount`. - the caller must have allowance for ``sender``'s tokens of at least `amount`.

updateAPP(address).details: set the new address of the Approved Price Providers(APP)

updateBase(uint256).details: set the base amount of the token. important for tokens that have more or less then 18 decimal places

updateDAOBetFee(uint256).details: set the fee users pay to buy an option

params.daoBetFee_: the new fee (in tenth percent) to buy an option

updateExerciserFee(uint256).details: set the fee users can recieve for exercising other users options

params.exerciserFee_: the new fee (in tenth percent) for exercising a options itm

updateExpirerFee(uint256).details: set the fee users can recieve for expiring other users options

params.expirerFee_: the new fee (in tenth percent) for expiring a options

updateMaxT(uint256).details: update the max rounds for option bets

params.newMax_: the new maximum time (in rounds) an option may be created for (inclusive).

updateMinT(uint256).details: update the min rounds for option bets

params.newMin_: the new minimum rounds (in rounds) an option may be created for (inclusive).

updateOwner(address).details: set the new address to control this contract

updatePoolLockSeconds(uint256).details: update the pool stake lock up time.

params.newLockSeconds_: the new lock time, in seconds

updateTreasury(address).details: set the new address of the treasury that early withdraw fees or bet fees go to

withdraw(uint256).details: recieve tokens from the pool.  If the current time is before your next available withdraw a 1% fee will be applied.

params.amount_: The amount of LP token to return the pool (burn).
